productDesc: Bakso is savory meatball and noodle soup. Also has hard boiled eggs and other potential add-ins like tofu or bok choy.
Mi goreng is a stir-fried noodle dish with a thick and flavorful sauce. You can pick your choice of chicken, beef, shrimp, or all three.
Nasi goreng is Indonesia's version of fried rice. Packs more flavor you can pick your choice of chicken, beef, shrimp, or all three. Topped with a fried egg.
Satay ayam is a chicken skewer marinated in sweet soy sauce and grilled over a flame. Served with a spicy peanut sauce.
Soto is an Indonesian chicken soup with a nice herbal broth and rice noodles, chicken, hard boiled eggs, and other various toppings.
Martabak telur is a savory roti-like fried pancake stuffed with a beef and egg filling. Very popular on the streets of Indonesia.
